    "explanation": "<p>The correct answer is:  </p>\n<p>✅ <strong>Option C: Bisphenol and phosgene</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n<p>Polycarbonates are produced by the reaction of <strong>bisphenol A (BPA)</strong> with <strong>phosgene (COCl₂)</strong>.  </p>\n<p>The reaction forms carbonate linkages (–O–CO–O–) in the polymer backbone, giving the polymer its name and characteristic toughness and transparency.</p>",
