    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Identify linear polymer from following.</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "<p>High density polymer</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "<p>Low density polymer</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "<p>Bakelite</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "<p>Melamine</p>"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<ul>\n<li><p><strong>Option A: High density polymer (HDPE)</strong>  </p>\n<p>→ High density polyethylene is <strong>a linear polymer</strong>. The chains are closely packed because of minimal branching.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Option B: Low density polymer (LDPE)</strong>  </p>\n<p>→ Low density polyethylene is <strong>highly branched</strong>, not linear.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Option C: Bakelite</strong>  </p>\n<p>→ This is a thermosetting polymer that is <strong>cross-linked</strong>, not linear.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Option D: Melamine</strong>  </p>\n<p>→ Also a thermosetting, <strong>cross-linked polymer</strong>.</p></li>\n</ul>\n<p>✅ <strong>Correct Answer: Option A — High density polymer (HDPE)</strong></p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2025,
    "yearKey": "mht-cet-pcb-2025-9th-april-morning-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Which from the following statements about nylon 2-nylon 6 is NOT correct?</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": " It is a polyester fibre\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": " It is a copolymer\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": " It is obtained from amino acids\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": " It is biodegradable"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Statement that is NOT correct about nylon 2-nylon 6 is:</p>\n<p><strong>Option A: It is a polyester fibre</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Nylon 2-nylon 6</strong> is not a polyester fibre; it is a <strong>polyamide fibre</strong> because its repeating units are joined by amide ($–CONH–$) bonds, not ester bonds ($–COO–$).</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Now let's check other options:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><p><strong>Option B:</strong> <em>It is a copolymer</em> — Correct. Nylon 2-nylon 6 is made from two different monomers (glycine and caprolactam).</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Option C:</strong> <em>It is obtained from amino acids</em> — Correct. It is made from glycine (an amino acid) and caprolactam.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Option D:</strong> <em>It is biodegradable</em> — Correct. Because it is made from amino acids, it is biodegradable.</p></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Final Answer:</strong>  </p>\n<p><strong>Option A is NOT correct.</strong></p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2024,
    "yearKey": "mht-cet-pcb-2024-22th-april-evening-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  },
