  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Which from following is a semisynthetic polymer?</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": " Silk\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": " Terylene\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": " Viscose rayon\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": " Neoprene"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "C"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Semisynthetic polymers are those obtained by chemically modifying a natural polymer. Let’s examine each option:</p>\n\n<p><p>Silk  </p>\n<p>– A natural protein fibre produced by silkworms.  </p>\n<p>– Not chemically modified from another polymer.</p></p>\n<p><p>Terylene  </p>\n<p>– A completely synthetic polyester (polyethylene terephthalate).  </p>\n<p>– Made from petrochemicals, not from a natural polymer.</p></p>\n<p><p>Viscose rayon  </p>\n<p>– Prepared by treating natural cellulose (from wood pulp or cotton) with chemicals (caustic soda, CS₂) and then regenerating it as fibres.  </p>\n<p>– Since it starts from a natural polymer (cellulose) and is chemically modified, it is semisynthetic.</p></p>\n<p><p>Neoprene  </p>\n<p>– A fully synthetic rubber (polychloroprene) made from petroleum derivatives.  </p>\n<p>– Not based on a natural polymer.</p></p>\n\n<p>Therefore, the semisynthetic polymer is:  </p>\n<p>Option C: Viscose rayon.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2024,
    "yearKey": "mht-cet-pcb-2024-22th-april-morning-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Which among the following is a monomer of natural rubber?</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "2-Methyl-1, 3-butadiene\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "1,1,2,2-Tetrafluoroethene\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "2-Chloro-1, 3 butadiene\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "1,3-butadiene"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Natural rubber is a polymer made up of repeating units of isoprene. Let’s see why option A is correct:</p>\n\n<p><p>Definition of monomer  </p>\n<p>– A monomer is a small molecule that can join together to form a polymer.  </p></p>\n<p><p>Natural rubber composition  </p>\n<p>– Natural rubber is “cis-1,4-polyisoprene.”  </p>\n<p>– Its repeating unit (monomer) is isoprene, whose systematic name is 2-methyl-1,3-butadiene.  </p></p>\n<p><p>Structure of isoprene  </p>\n<p>– In condensed form: CH₂=C(CH₃)–CH=CH₂  </p>\n<p>– IUPAC name: 2-methyl-1,3-butadiene  </p></p>\n<p><p>Checking the options  </p>\n<p>A. 2-Methyl-1,3-butadiene → isoprene → monomer of natural rubber  </p>\n<p>B. 1,1,2,2-Tetrafluoroethene → monomer of Teflon (a fluoropolymer)  </p>\n<p>C. 2-Chloro-1,3-butadiene → chloroprene → monomer of Neoprene (synthetic rubber)  </p>\n<p>D. 1,3-Butadiene → monomer of polybutadiene (synthetic rubber)  </p></p>\n\n<p>Answer: Option A (2-Methyl-1,3-butadiene) is the monomer of natural rubber.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2024,
    "yearKey": "mht-cet-pcb-2024-22th-april-morning-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  }
]